context.arch.intelligibility
Class StaticExplainerDelegate

java.lang.Object
  context.arch.intelligibility.StaticExplainerDelegate

public abstract class StaticExplainerDelegate
extends java.lang.Object

Delegate class for Explainers useful for Explainers that generate explanations that are fixed once the model is non-changing. I.e., all explanations can be pre-generated once the model is final. If the model is updated (e.g. for dynamic training), then the explanations can be "refreshed". Explanations are be pre-generated by parsing the original model, and building a Disjunctive Normal Form expression (as a Disjunction). The model-dependent explanations can be obtained by reading this data structure.

Contrast this with Explainers that can only generate explanations depending on the input states (e.g. NaiveBayesExplainer, HmmExplainer).

This is an abstract class that needs to be subclassed to implement a way to build the DNF reasons for each outcome value.

See Also:
RulesExplainer, J48Explainer

getReasonsDNF

protected java.util.Map<java.lang.String,DNF> getReasonsDNF()
Creates the reasons for all outcome values. This would be model-dependent, and parsed from the underlying model. Note that this may be called many times, so keep it light-weight.

Parameters:
init - if true, then it refreshes, and may use heavy-weight parsing to create the reasons; if false, then it reuses the previously stored reasons
Returns:
map where each key is an outcome value, and each value is the DNF Expression for that outcome value.
